Output (b), on the other hand, focuses more on the steps and requirements to become a licensed electrician, which is a part of the process but not the entire journey. While Output (b) provides some useful information, it does not cover the broader aspects of becoming an electrician, such as foundational knowledge, certifications, and soft skills.  Therefore, Output (a) is better. END OF Decision
